The House of Representatives Committee on Works yesterday advised the government to reduce the volume of road construction contracts currently being handled by construction giant, Julius Berger. The committee further alleged that Julius Berger was unprofessional in the handling of the Second Niger Bridge, the Lagos-Ibadan and the Abuja-Kaduna-Zaria-Kano road projects, saying it will be impossible for them to complete or commission the projects as expected by President Muhammadu Buhari’s administration. The committee chairman, Abubakar Kabir, (APC-Kano), made the disclosure yesterday after receiving the submission of the contractor, Julius Berger on the three projects. “At the rate at which the slow pace of work is going on, there is no way that President Buhari will commission the Second Niger Bridge, Lagos-Ibadan Express Way, Abuja-Kaduna-Zaria-Kani Road during his tenure,” he said. According to him, despite collecting more than N200 billion, Julius Berger is still yet to do substantial work on the projects. “We are recommending that these projects should be split and awarded to other companies, because we don’t think Julius Berger alone can handle them. “The 2nd Niger Bridge, was awarded for N206,151,693billion, the Kaduna-Abuja Road, was awarded for N155 billion, while the 1st section of the Lagos-Ibadan road was awarded for N134 billion,” he added.